100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 30, 1926, the British Parliament debated a new measure to address the ongoing economic struggles post-World War I, seeking to stabilize the nations finances. In the United States, President Calvin Coolidge delivered a speech emphasizing the importance of business growth as a pillar of national prosperity. Meanwhile, the League of Nations continued its discussions on disarmament, reflecting the global desire for lasting peace.
